==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ear-minded
<hw>Ear"-mind"ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Physiol.
Psychol.)</fld> <def>Thinking chiefly or most readily through, or in
terms related to, the sense of hearing; specif., thinking words as
spoken, as a result of familiarity with speech or of mental peculiarity;
-- opposed to <contr>eye-minded</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Earn</ent>⟦br⟧
